solutionCode.javascript:
    ```javascript
function finalValue(nums, original) {
    while (nums.includes(original)) {
        original++;
    }
    return original;
}
```

    The algorithm is pretty straightforward for all implementations. Declare function `finalValue` that accepts an array of integers `nums` and an integer `original` as input arguments.

Then, execute a while loop which continues until `original` is not found in the `nums` array. Inside the while loop, increment the value of the `original` by 1 (+1) for each iteration.

Once the loop ends, return the final value of `original`.

Note that the algorithm is almost the same for each programming language, with only minor syntax adjustments needed.

solutionCode.java:
    ```java
int finalValue(int[] nums, int original) {
    boolean found = true;
    while (found) {
        found = false;
        for (int num : nums) {
            if (num == original) {
                original++;
                found = true;
                break;
            }
        }
    }
    return original;
}
```

